---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy | WasteWize UK"
  description="WasteWize UK Cookie Policy. Learn how we use cookies to improve our waste management services and website performance."
>

  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home",          "item": "https://wastewize.co.uk/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Cookie Policy", "item": "https://wastewize.co.uk/cookies" }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>
  <main class="bg-brand-dark text-white min-h-screen">
    <section class="py-20 px-6 border-b border-white/5 bg-brand-dark-card">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-4">Cookie <span class="text-brand-lime">Policy</span></h1>
        <p class="text-white/40 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm italic">Last Updated: May 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-12 text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
            <p>
              Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit our website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, as well as to provide information to the owners of the site.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
            <p>WasteWize UK uses cookies to enhance your experience in the following ways:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Necessary for the website to function, such as security features or load balancing.</li>
              <li><strong>Performance & Analytics:</strong> To understand how visitors interact with our site (e.g., which pages are most popular) so we can improve our service descriptions.</li>
              <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> To remember choices you make, such as details entered into our quote request forms.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Cookies We Use</h3>
            <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
              <thead class="border-b border-white/10 text-brand-lime uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">
                <tr>
                  <th class="pb-4">Cookie Type</th>
                  <th class="pb-4">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="pb-4">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-white/60">
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                  <td class="py-4 font-semibold text-white">Security</td>
                  <td class="py-4">Protects against cross-site request forgery on forms.</td>
                  <td class="py-4">Session</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                  <td class="py-4 font-semibold text-white">Analytics</td>
                  <td class="py-4">Anonymous data on how you arrived at our site.</td>
                  <td class="py-4">24 Months</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-4 font-semibold text-white">Preferences</td>
                  <td class="py-4">Remembers your cookie consent status.</td>
                  <td class="py-4">12 Months</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">3. Managing Your Cookies</h2>
            <p>
              Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can set your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, please note that some parts of our website may not function properly if you disable cookies.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              To find out more about cookies, including how to see what cookies have been set, visit <a href="https://www.aboutcookies.org" class="text-brand-lime hover:underline" target="_blank">www.aboutcookies.org</a>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">4. More Information</h2>
            <p>
              If you have any questions about our use of cookies, please contact us at our registered office: <br/>
              <strong>9 Cordelia Court, Burns Lane, London, NW7 2GB</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>

        <div class="mt-20 pt-10 border-t border-white/10 text-center">
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-sm text-brand-lime hover:underline italic">View Full Privacy Policy</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>